<title>USA: Drypers to amend senior bond terms.</title>
<headline>Drypers to amend senior bond terms.</headline>
<dateline>HOUSTON 1996-09-04</dateline>
<text>
<p>Drypers Corp said on Wednesday it has received consents from a majority of noteholders to amend the indenture covering its 12-1/2 percent senior notes.</p>
<p>The changes will make it easier for Drypers' international expasnion by allowing use of equity capital to fund growth, Drypers said.</p>
<p>As a result of the changes in the note, the company intends to proceed with current joint venture arrangements in Brazil and Mexico, said Drypers, a maker of disposable diapers and related products.</p>
